  "design_rationale": "This storage design is optimized for the TPC-H analytical workload targeting execution time minimization. Key decisions: (1) Binary columnar format enables column pruning (50-75% I/O reduction) and mmap-based zero-copy access. (2) Sort lineitem by l_shipdate because all 3 queries filter on this column, enabling zone map block skipping (skip 80-90% of blocks in Q6). (3) Block size of 100K rows (~780KB per column) fits well in L3 cache (44MB / 64 cores = ~680KB per core). (4) Dictionary encoding for low-cardinality columns (l_returnflag, l_linestatus, c_mktsegment, status flags) reduces memory by 75-90% and enables integer comparisons. (5) Zone maps on all frequently-filtered numeric columns (l_shipdate, l_discount, l_quantity, o_orderdate) enable aggressive block pruning on HDD storage. (6) Hash indexes on all primary keys and foreign keys enable O(1) join probing. (7) Parallel ingestion with 64-way parallelism leverages all CPU cores for fast data loading (<45s for SF1). (8) No pre-loading: each query mmaps only its needed columns on-demand, minimizing memory footprint and startup time. Expected query speedup: 8-10x from parallelism, 3-5x from columnar I/O reduction, 2-10x from zone map pruning = 50-500x total vs naive single-threaded row-store with text parsing.",
